# CombatMode Architecture and Style

Use this project map and conventions for all changes.

## Runtime structure

- `CombatMode/CombatMode.toc`: addon metadata, `SavedVariables: CombatModeDB`, load order entrypoint.
- `CombatMode/Embeds.xml`: loads Lua files and owns the root frame scripts (`OnEvent`, `OnUpdate` bridge).
- `CombatMode/Constants/*.lua`: constants and static tables (`CM.Constants`).
- `CombatMode/Core/*.lua`: runtime systems and gameplay behavior.
- `CombatMode/Config/*.lua`: AceConfig option builders and category assembly.
- `CombatMode/UI/CrosshairEditMode.lua`: Edit Mode integration for crosshair controls.
- `CombatMode/Bindings.xml`: keybinding declarations and binding click targets.

## Module responsibilities

- `Core/Runtime.lua`: owns addon lifecycle (`OnInitialize`/`OnEnable`/`OnDisable`), cross-feature coordination points, global `CombatMode_OnUpdate`, first-login welcome `StaticPopup`, and deferred in-game changelog open (`ScheduleChangelogIfNewVersion` → `CM.Config.MaybeShowChangelogOnNewVersion`) when `CM.DB.global.lastSeenChangelogVersion` ≠ `CM.METADATA["VERSION"]`.
- `Core/RuntimeEventRouter.lua`: owns centralized event category dispatch and `_G.CombatMode_OnEvent`; builds/owns `eventCategoryMap`.
- `Core/RuntimeCVarManager.lua`: owns all addon-owned **CVar writes** (centralized `CM.SetCVar*` helpers) and the feature-level CVar helpers (reticle targeting presets merged with `CM.DB.global.reticleTargetingCVarOverrides` via `CM.GetEffectiveReticleTargetingCVarValues`, Interaction HUD soft-target subset, action camera, sticky crosshair, shoulder offset, mouselook speed) and reset-to-default.
- `Core/RuntimeBindingQueue.lua`: owns combat-safe deferred binding write queue (`CM.TryApplyBindingChange`, `CM.FlushDeferredBindingChanges`).
- `Core/RuntimeBootstrap.lua`: owns startup wiring (`CM.BootstrapFeatureModules`) that initializes Core systems in the same sequence as Runtime enable.
- `Core/FreeLookController.lua`: owns free-look/mouselook state transitions, cursor-mode keybind behavior, and UI side effects tied to lock/unlock flow.
- `Constants/ConstantsNamespace.lua`: initializes the `CM.Constants` namespace only.
- `Constants/Constants*.lua`: define immutable/static tables (defaults, CVars, event groups, assets, watchlists, radial metadata); no runtime side effects beyond table population.
- `Core/Crosshair.lua`: owns crosshair visuals and reaction logic. Crosshair reaction and cursor centering follow `CM.IsCrosshairEnabled()`.
- `Core/BindingOverrides.lua`: owns override binding/macro synthesis for mouse buttons and modified clicks; refreshes when bars/bindings change.
- `Core/AddonActionBarResolver.lua`: owns third-party action bar button resolution by action-slot id (ElvUI/Bartender4).
- `Core/TargetingMacroBuilder.lua`: owns reticle-targeting macro text construction (pre-line, /click wrapper, @cursor handling). Exports `CM.TargetingMacroPrelinesDefaults`; honors account-wide `CM.DB.global.targetingMacroPrelineAnyOverride` / `targetingMacroPrelineEnemyOverride` when set.
- `Core/AutoCursorUnlock.lua`: owns unlock predicates (frame visibility, mounts, pet battle, custom expression) and wildcard frame tracking.
- `Core/Animations.lua`: owns user-facing animations (cursor pulse after unlock/free-look transitions; crosshair reaction/lock-in presentation).
- `Core/InteractionHUD.lua`: owns the Interaction HUD widget lifecycle, fade/range `OnUpdate`, and soft-interact event handling.
- `Core/HealingRadial.lua`: owns radial frame lifecycle, selection tracking, secure cast attributes, and group/role slice updates.
- `UI/CrosshairEditMode.lua`: owns Edit Mode registration, option controls, and persisted layout integration for the crosshair UI.
- `Config/ConfigNamespace.lua`: initializes the `CM.Config` namespace only.
- `Config/ConfigShared.lua`: shared AceConfig builders/helpers used by all config category modules (includes `Header`/`Description` key `prelines` for the preline editor).
- `Config/ReticleCVarEditorData.lua`: reticle CVar editor row data and override persistence helpers.
- `Config/ReticleCVarEditorPanel.lua`: custom Reticle Targeting CVar editor UI; `CM.OpenReticleTargetingCVarEditor()`.
- `Config/TargetingMacroPrelinesEditor.lua`: `AceConfigDialog` for editing click-cast preline overrides; `CM.OpenTargetingMacroPrelinesEditor()`; opened from `ConfigReticleTargeting.lua`.
- `Config/ConfigChangelogData.lua`: holds `CM.Config.ChangelogText` (markdown string for the in-game viewer); keep in sync with `CombatMode/CHANGELOG.md` via `scripts/sync-changelog-to-lua.ps1`.
- `Config/ConfigChangelogPanel.lua`: changelog popup UI (`SimpleHTML` + `ScrollFrame`); `CM.Config.ShowChangelog`, `CM.Config.MaybeShowChangelogOnNewVersion`; sets `CM.DB.global.lastSeenChangelogVersion` when shown. Called from `ConfigAbout.lua` and scheduled in `Core/Runtime.lua` on login after version changes.
- `Config/Config*.lua` (feature files): define option tables, read/write DB values, and call existing feature APIs (no duplicated feature logic).
- `Config/ConfigCategories.lua`: assembles category roots and registration metadata consumed by Core during options setup.

## Required coding conventions

- **Lua global localization header convention**
  - Keep global aliases per-file; do not create a shared/global alias module (for example, no `CM.API` globals table).
  - Header order:
    1. `_G`, `LibStub`, addon handle (`CM`)
    2. WoW API globals
    3. Lua stdlib aliases (`pairs`, `ipairs`, `type`, `pcall`, `math`, etc.)
    4. module-local constants
  - Localize only symbols used in that file.
  - Remove unused aliases when touching a file.
  - Prefer function alias style (`local strfind = _G.string.find`) unless many members from the table are used.
- Keep event wiring centralized via constants and core dispatch; avoid ad-hoc event frames.
- Prefer extending existing `CM` feature APIs over introducing new global state.
- Respect combat lockdown and secure action patterns (`SecureActionButtonTemplate`, macro attributes).
- Use existing DB scopes consistently:
  - account-wide in `CM.DB.global`
  - character-specific in `CM.DB.char`
- Put new user-facing settings in `Config/Config*.lua` and wire through `Config/ConfigCategories.lua`.
- Preserve slash command and keybinding behavior unless change is explicitly requested.
- Lua validation default is changed-files pre-commit: `pre-commit run --files <changed files>`.
- Use direct formatter/linter commands only for targeted debugging.
- Run repo-wide gate only for release prep or explicit maintainer request: `pre-commit run --all-files`.

## Change expectations

- Follow current file header purpose comments as source of truth for module intent.
- Keep edits minimal and local to the owning module.
- Call out behavior changes that affect mouselook, targeting CVars, or binding overrides.
